It also involves the study of state-of-the-art Encoder-Decoder architectures, which is a common technique used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, the paper proposes a new universal decoder to improve semantic segmentation accuracy, which is a key aspect of computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the training of deep learning models in an end-to-end fashion. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes a new method to improve the accuracy of deep learning models, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence research. 

The Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is another possibility as the paper deals with biomedical image segmentation, which is a type of multimedia data. 

Finally, the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category is a possibility as the paper involves the use of deep learning models, which are a type of neural network.
